                       Report Code Configuration Help            Page 1 of 4
 
      A report code is a description of a statistical report which
      will be generated by the stations on the Distributed Network.
      The report code configuration is the lowest level description
      sent, informing the station to return specific statistics.
      All report codes are grouped into report classes, which are
      used for the station configuration. This menu allows report
      code functions to be performed, including: adding, modifying,
      deleting, and listing report codes.
 
      Adding A Report Code
      ====================
      To add a report code to the Distributed Network, enter "1" (for
      Add Report Code), and press return.  The program will then prompt
      for the report code number.  Enter the code number and press
      return.  If the code already exists, an error message will be
      displayed, and you will be prompted for another code.  If the
      code does not exist, the Add a Report Code screen will be
      displayed, requiring the report code configuration to be input.
 
