      Deleting a Report Code (cont'd)
      ===============================
      To delete a code, enter "3" and press return.  Enter the code number,
      and if it exists, the Delete a Code screen will be displayed.
      If the code does not exist, an error message will be displayed, and
      you must re-enter the code number.  Once the Delete Screen has been
      displayed, look at the configuration information to ensure that this
      is the correct code.  If you wish to delete it, enter "Y" and press
      return, and a message will be displayed informing that the code
      was deleted.  If you no not wish to delete the code, enter "N" and
      the code will not be deleted.
 
      Listing Report Codes
      ====================
      This option will allow all report codes to be displayed.  The
      user also has the ability to scroll forward or back, to view the
      desired information.
 
      For more information refer to Report Code Listing help.
